<p>Minimal doesn't necessarily mean "simple"</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;/section&gt;

&lt;section&gt; Minimal could mean: * Constrained * Underfunded * Fewer total number of technologies * Easier to maintain long-term * Fewer &lt;strong&gt;"dependencies"&lt;/strong&gt; * Formats that are &lt;strong&gt;"future proofed"&lt;/strong&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Read more about Minimal Computing here: 
Keep in mind that open source tools are <br /> free as in kitten not free as in beer.</p>

<p>Technical debt</p>

<p>Higher likelihood that it will keep working into the future because of simpler component parts with fewer dependencies.</p>

<h1 id="wax">Wax</h1>
<p>Wax is a minimal computing publishing tool for the creation of academic digital exhibits using a IIIF viewer.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Leveraged <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/" target="_blank">Jekyll</a> and Github Pages</li>
  <li>Uses <a href="https://iiif.io/" target="_blank">IIIF (International Image Interoperability Framework)(<a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1h9SPg9nlLA3TAdzkYxkyaFFNNf8m4PsbaIExcYwVLyo/edit#heading=h.q7mmne7d3bk2" target="_blank">why IIIF?</a>)&lt;/li&gt;
  <li>Uses <a href="https://openseadragon.github.io/" target="_blank">OpenSeaDragon</a> viewer but can use any other</li>
  <li>Creates a relatively small static site (vs. dynamic)</li>
&lt;/ul&gt;

# CollectionBuilder
